  - Butterfly also reads as more lead‑vocal/front‑single focused rather than explicitly harmony‑forward or decade‑spanning in sequencing; given my specific appetite for lush stacked harmonies and cohesive album sequencing that preserves transient snap, the Archival remaster better fulfills the full set of priorities rather than a narrower set of club‑single strengths.
